{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850476932,"sessionID":"ses_287109f05ffeMz4NppqMghejZ3","part":{"id":"prt_d78efd55b001X48nMlEpnVrSPh","messageID":"msg_d78efc34b001TYstk0S93A2t7F","sessionID":"ses_287109f05ffeMz4NppqMghejZ3","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-4a77c88c16914198b02a63e20fac3678","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/router` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Error Types & Interfaces (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1**: Define error types in `errors.go`\n20:   - `SessionNotFoundError` with `SessionID` field, code `SESSION_NOT_FOUND`, HTTP 404\n21:   - `SandboxUnreachableError` with `SandboxID` field, code `SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE`, HTTP 502\n22:   - `SandboxTimeoutError` with `SandboxID` field, code `SANDBOX_TIMEOUT`, HTTP 504\n23:   - `JWTSigningError` with `Err` field, code `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED`, HTTP 500\n24:   - `ServerOverloadedError` with code `SERVER_OVERLOADED`, HTTP 429\n25:   - `NoEntryPointError` with code `NO_ENTRY_POINT`, HTTP 404\n26:   - All errors implement `APIStatus` interface: `Status() int`, `Code() string`, `Message() string`\n27:   - File: `pkg/router/errors.go`\n28:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestErrorTypes -v`\n29: \n30: - [ ] **T1.2**: Define `APIStatus` interface\n31:   - Methods: `Status() int`, `Code() string`, `Message() string`\n32:   - All error types implement this interface\n33:   - File: `pkg/router/errors.go`\n34:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestAPIStatus -v`\n35: \n36: ### Phase 2: Config & Constants (ST-2)\n37: \n38: - [ ] **T2.1**: Define `Config` struct in `config.go`\n39:   - `Port int` (default 8080)\n40:   - `EnableTLS bool`\n41:   - `TLSCert string`\n42:   - `TLSKey string`\n43:   - `MaxConcurrentRequests int` (default 1000)\n44:   - `Debug bool`\n45:   - File: `pkg/router/config.go`\n46:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConfig -v`\n47: \n48: - [ ] **T2.2**: Implement `DefaultConfig()` function\n49:   - Returns `Config{Port: 8080, EnableTLS: false, MaxConcurrentRequests: 1000}`\n50:   - File: `pkg/router/config.go`\n51:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestDefaultConfig -v`\n52: \n53: - [ ] **T2.3**: Define constants in `jwt.go`\n54:   - `rsaKeySize = 2048`\n55:   - `jwtExpiration = 5 * time.Minute`\n56:   - `IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"`\n57:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n58:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConstants -v`\n59: \n60: ### Phase 3: Store Interface & Logger (ST-3)\n61: \n62: - [ ] **T3.1**: Define `Store` interface for router\n63:   - `GetSession(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n64:   - `CreateSession(ctx, sandboxInfo) error`\n65:   - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID) error`\n66:   - File: `pkg/router/store.go` (or import from pkg/store)\n67:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestStoreInterface -v`\n68: \n69: - [ ] **T3.2**: Define `Logger` interface\n70:   - Methods: `Info(msg, keysAndValues...)`, `Error(msg, keysAndValues...)`, `Warning(msg, keysAndValues...)`\n71:   - File: `pkg/router/logger.go`\n72:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestLoggerInterface -v`\n73: \n74: ### Phase 4: JWTManager (ST-4)\n75: \n76: - [ ] **T4.1**: Define `JWTManager` interface\n77:   - `GenerateToken(ctx, kind, name, namespace) (string, error)`\n78:   - `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx) error`\n79:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n80:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerInterface -v`\n81: \n82: - [ ] **T4.2**: Define `jwtManager` struct\n83:   - `privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey`\n84:   - `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey`\n85:   - `kubeClient kubernetes.Interface`\n86:   - `namespace string`\n87:   - `logger Logger`\n88:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n89:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerStruct -v`\n90: \n91: - [ ] **T4.3**: Implement RSA key generation\n92:   - `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)`\n93:   - Private key: PKCS1 PEM encoding\n94:   - Public key: PKIX PEM encoding\n95:   - Helper functions: `encodePrivateKeyPEM`, `encodePublicKeyPEM`, `loadPrivateKeyPEM`\n96:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n97:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestRSAKeyGeneration -v`\n98: \n99: - [ ] **T4.4**: Implement `NewJWTManager(kubeClient, namespace, logger)` constructor\n100:   - Generate RSA 2048-bit key pair\n101:   - Initialize struct with all fields\n102:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n103:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewJWTManager -v`\n104: \n105: - [ ] **T4.5**: Implement `GenerateToken(ctx, kind, name, namespace)` method\n106:   - Create JWT with claims: `exp` (now+5m), `iat` (now), `iss=\"agentcube-router\"`\n107:   - Add custom claims: `kind`, `name`, `namespace`\n108:   - Sign with RS256 algorithm\n109:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n110:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManager_GenerateToken -v`\n111: \n112: - [ ] **T4.6**: Implement `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)` method\n113:   - Create K8s Secret with name `picod-router-identity`\n114:   - Handle `AlreadyExists` by loading existing secret\n115:   - Load keys from secret data\n116:   - Use `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env var (default \"default\")\n117:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n118:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManager_TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret -v`\n119: \n120: ### Phase 5: SessionManager (ST-5)\n121: \n122: - [ ] **T5.1**: Define `SessionManager` interface\n123:   - `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n124:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n125:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionManagerInterface -v`\n126: \n127: - [ ] **T5.2**: Define `manager` struct\n128:   - `storeClient Store`\n129:   - `workloadMgrAddr string`\n130:   - `httpClient *http.Client`\n131:   - `logger Logger`\n132:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n133:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestManagerStruct -v`\n134: \n135: - [ ] **T5.3**: Implement `NewSessionManager(store, logger)` constructor\n136:   - Read `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env var (required, fail if missing)\n137:   - Configure HTTP client: `Timeout=2m`, `MaxIdleConnsPerHost=100`\n138:   - Configure HTTP2: `ReadIdleTimeout=30s`, `PingTimeout=15s`\n139:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n140:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewSessionManager -v`\n141: \n142: - [ ] **T5.4**: Implement `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)` method\n143:   - If `sessionID` empty: call `createSandbox(ctx, namespace, name, kind)`\n144:   - If `sessionID` present: call `storeClient.GetSession(ctx, sessionID)`\n145:   - Return `SandboxInfo` or error\n146:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n147:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession -v`\n148: \n149: - [ ] **T5.5**: Implement `createSandbox(ctx, namespace, name, kind)` internal method\n150:   - Build `CreateSandboxRequest` with Kind, Name, Namespace\n151:   - POST to `/v1/agent-runtime` for `AgentRuntimeKind`\n152:   - POST to `/v1/code-interpreter` for `CodeInterpreterKind`\n153:   - Add K8s SA token from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` if available\n154:   - Parse `CreateSandboxResponse` and store via `CreateSession`\n155:   - Use namespace from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env var (default \"default\")\n156:   - File: `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n157:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSessionManager_createSandbox -v`\n158: \n159: ### Phase 6: Middleware (ST-6)\n160: \n161: - [ ] **T6.1**: Implement `concurrencyLimitMiddleware(maxConcurrent)` function\n162:   - Use buffered channel as semaphore\n163:   - Capacity = `maxConcurrent` (default 1000 if <=0)\n164:   - `sem <- struct{}{}` to acquire slot\n165:   - `<-sem` to release slot (deferred)\n166:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n167:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConcurrencyLimitMiddleware -v`\n168: \n169: - [ ] **T6.2**: Implement 429 overload response\n170:   - `select` with `default` case when semaphore full\n171:   - Return HTTP 429 with `{\"error\": \"server overloaded\", \"code\": \"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"}`\n172:   - Call `c.Abort()` to stop processing\n173:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n174:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConcurrencyLimitMiddleware_Overload -v`\n175: \n176: - [ ] **T6.3**: Implement `loggingMiddleware` function\n177:   - Log request method, path, status, duration\n178:   - Use `logger.Info` with keys: method, path, status, duration\n179:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n180:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestLoggingMiddleware -v`\n181: \n182: - [ ] **T6.4**: Implement `recoveryMiddleware` function\n183:   - Recover from panics\n184:   - Log error with stack trace\n185:   - Return HTTP 500 with `{\"error\": \"internal server error\"}`\n186:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n187:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestRecoveryMiddleware -v`\n188: \n189: ### Phase 7: Reverse Proxy (ST-7)\n190: \n191: - [ ] **T7.1**: Implement `newReverseProxy(target, jwt, sessionID)` function\n192:   - Use `httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy(target)`\n193:   - Set custom `Director` function\n194:   - Set custom `ModifyResponse` function\n195:   - Set custom `ErrorHandler` function\n196:   - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n197:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReverseProxy -v`\n198: \n199: - [ ] **T7.2**: Implement `Director` function\n200:   - Path normalization: add leading `/` if missing\n201:   - Set `req.URL.Scheme`, `req.URL.Host`, `req.URL.Path`\n202:   - Set `req.Host` to target host\n203:   - Set forwarding headers: `X-Forwarded-Host`, `X-Forwarded-Proto`, `X-Forwarded-For`, `X-Real-IP`\n204:   - Inject JWT: `Authorization: Bearer <jwt>`\n205:   - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n206:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReverseProxy_Director -v`\n207: \n208: - [ ] **T7.3**: Implement `ModifyResponse` function\n209:   - Add `x-agentcube-session-id` header to response\n210:   - Value is the resolved session ID\n211:   - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n212:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReverseProxy_ModifyResponse -v`\n213: \n214: - [ ] **T7.4**: Implement `ErrorHandler` function\n215:   - Check for \"connection refused\" → HTTP 502 `sandbox unreachable`\n216:   - Check for \"timeout\" → HTTP 504 `sandbox timeout`\n217:   - Other errors → HTTP 500\n218:   - Return JSON response: `{\"error\": \"<message>\"}`\n219:   - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n220:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReverseProxy_ErrorHandler -v`\n221: \n222: - [ ] **T7.5**: Implement `selectEntryPoint(entryPoints, invocationPath)` helper\n223:   - Find matching entry point by path prefix\n224:   - Default to first entry point if no match\n225:   - Return nil if `entryPoints` is empty\n226:   - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n227:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestSelectEntryPoint -v`\n228: \n229: - [ ] **T7.6**: Implement `buildTargetURL(entryPoint)` helper\n230:   - Parse `entryPoint.Endpoint` as URL\n231:   - Add protocol prefix if missing: `entryPoint.Protocol + \"://\" + endpoint`\n232:   - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n233:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestBuildTargetURL -v`\n234: \n235: ### Phase 8: Handlers (ST-8)\n236: \n237: - [ ] **T8.1**: Implement `handleHealthLive(c)` handler\n238:   - Return HTTP 200\n239:   - Body: `{\"status\": \"alive\"}`\n240:   - File: `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n241:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandleHealthLive -v`\n242: \n243: - [ ] **T8.2**: Implement `handleHealthReady(c)` handler\n244:   - Check if `sessionManager != nil`\n245:   - If nil: HTTP 503, body: `{\"status\": \"not ready\", \"error\": \"session manager not available\"}`\n246:   - If valid: HTTP 200, body: `{\"status\": \"ready\"}`\n247:   - File: `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n248:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandleHealthReady -v`\n249: \n250: - [ ] **T8.3**: Implement `handleInvoke(c)` handler for invocation routing\n251:   - Extract `namespace`, `name`, `kind` from URL path params\n252:   - Extract `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n253:   - Call `sessionManager.GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)`\n254:   - Update activity: `storeClient.UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID)` (1st)\n255:   - Select entry point from `SandboxInfo.EntryPoints`\n256:   - Generate JWT via `jwtManager.GenerateToken(ctx, kind, name, namespace)`\n257:   - Create reverse proxy and serve\n258:   - Update activity after proxy (2nd)\n259:   - Inject `x-agentcube-session-id` response header\n260:   - Handle errors with appropriate HTTP codes\n261:   - File: `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n262:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandleInvoke -v`\n263: \n264: - [ ] **T8.4**: Implement `handleAgentInvoke(c)` handler\n265:   - Set `kind = AgentRuntimeKind`\n266:   - Delegate to `handleInvoke`\n267:   - File: `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n268:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandleAgentInvoke -v`\n269: \n270: - [ ] **T8.5**: Implement `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke(c)` handler\n271:   - Set `kind = CodeInterpreterKind`\n272:   - Delegate to `handleInvoke`\n273:   - File: `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n274:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandleCodeInterpreterInvoke -v`\n275: \n276: - [ ] **T8.6**: Implement `handleGetSandboxError(c, err)` helper\n277:   - Check `apierrors.IsNotFound` → HTTP 404\n278:   - Check `apierrors.APIStatus` → use status code from APIStatus\n279:   - Other errors → HTTP 500 with `\"internal server error\"`\n280:   - File: `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n281:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandleGetSandboxError -v`\n282: \n283: ### Phase 9: Server (ST-9)\n284: \n285: - [ ] **T9.1**: Define `Server` struct\n286:   - `config *Config`\n287:   - `engine *gin.Engine`\n288:   - `httpServer *http.Server`\n289:   - `sessionManager SessionManager`\n290:   - `storeClient Store`\n291:   - `jwtManager JWTManager`\n292:   - `transport *http.Transport`\n293:   - `logger Logger`\n294:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n295:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServerStruct -v`\n296: \n297: - [ ] **T9.2**: Implement `NewServer(config, sessionManager, store, jwtManager, logger)` constructor\n298:   - Create `engine := gin.New()`\n299:   - Set Gin mode: `gin.ReleaseMode` if `!config.Debug`, `gin.DebugMode` if `config.Debug`\n300:   - Initialize shared `http.Transport`\n301:   - Configure `httpServer` with h2c, `ReadTimeout=30s`, `IdleTimeout=90s`\n302:   - Register routes with middleware\n303:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n304:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewServer -v`\n305: \n306: - [ ] **T9.3**: Implement route registration\n307:   - `/health/live` → `handleHealthLive` (no middleware)\n308:   - `/health/ready` → `handleHealthReady` (no middleware)\n309:   - `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` → `handleAgentInvoke` (GET, POST)\n310:   - `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` → `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` (GET, POST)\n311:   - Apply middleware: `concurrencyLimitMiddleware`, `loggingMiddleware`, `recoveryMiddleware`\n312:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n313:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServer_Routes -v`\n314: \n315: - [ ] **T9.4**: Implement `Start(ctx)` method without TLS\n316:   - Configure h2c server with `http2.Server`\n317:   - Call `httpServer.ListenAndServe()`\n318:   - Launch goroutine for graceful shutdown on context cancel\n319:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n320:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServer_Start -v`\n321: \n322: - [ ] **T9.5**: Implement `Start(ctx)` method with TLS\n323:   - If `config.EnableTLS == true`: call `httpServer.ListenAndServeTLS(config.TLSCert, config.TLSKey)`\n324:   - Return error if cert/key files missing\n325:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n326:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServer_StartTLS -v`\n327: \n328: - [ ] **T9.6**: Implement graceful shutdown\n329:   - On context cancel: call `httpServer.Shutdown(shutdownCtx)`\n330:   - Shutdown deadline: 10s\n331:   - Server stops accepting new connections\n332:   - Existing connections complete before shutdown\n333:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n334:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServer_GracefulShutdown -v`\n335: \n336: - [ ] **T9.7**: Implement `Stop()` method\n337:   - Call `httpServer.Shutdown(ctx)` directly\n338:   - Use 10s timeout context\n339:   - File: `pkg/router/server.go`\n340:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServer_Stop -v`\n341: \n342: ### Phase 10: Integration Tests (ST-10)\n343: \n344: - [ ] **T10.1**: Implement `handleInvoke` integration test\n345:   - Test session resolution flow without session header → creates sandbox\n346:   - Test session resolution with valid session header → lookup from store\n347:   - Test session resolution with invalid session → 404 response\n348:   - File: `pkg/router/handlers_test.go`\n349:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestHandleInvoke_Integration -v`\n350: \n351: - [ ] **T10.2**: Implement proxy flow integration test\n352:   - Test successful proxy → response header with session ID\n353:   - Test sandbox unreachable → 502 response\n354:   - Test sandbox timeout → 504 response\n355:   - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go`\n356:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReverseProxy_Integration -v`\n357: \n358: - [ ] **T10.3**: Implement JWT injection test\n359:   - Test Sandbox/SandboxClaim kind → JWT in Authorization header\n360:   - Test AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter → no JWT (or verify behavior)\n361:   - File: `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go`\n362:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestReverseProxy_JWT -v`\n363: \n364: - [ ] **T10.4**: Implement concurrency limit integration test\n365:   - Test under limit → request processed\n366:   - Test at limit → 429 response\n367:   - Test semaphore release after request completes\n368:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware_test.go`\n369:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestConcurrencyLimit_Integration -v`\n370: \n371: - [ ] **T10.5**: Implement graceful shutdown integration test\n372:   - Test context cancel → shutdown within 10s deadline\n373:   - Test existing requests complete before shutdown\n374:   - File: `pkg/router/server_test.go`\n375:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestServer_GracefulShutdown_Integration -v`\n376: \n377: ### Phase 11: Mock Implementations (ST-11)\n378: \n379: - [ ] **T11.1**: Implement `MockStore` for testing\n380:   - `GetSessionFunc`, `CreateSessionFunc`, `UpdateSessionLastActivityFunc`\n381:   - Implement Store interface\n382:   - File: `pkg/router/mocks_test.go`\n383:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestMockStore -v`\n384: \n385: - [ ] **T11.2**: Implement `MockSessionManager` for testing\n386:   - `GetSandboxBySessionFunc`\n387:   - Implement SessionManager interface\n388:   - File: `pkg/router/mocks_test.go`\n389:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestMockSessionManager -v`\n390: \n391: - [ ] **T11.3**: Implement `MockJWTManager` for testing\n392:   - `GenerateTokenFunc`, `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecretFunc`\n393